meta {
  name: GET homeRegion (per-VIN base URI discovery, evcc port)
  type: http
  seq: 22
}

get {
  url: https://mal-1a.prd.ece.vwg-connect.com/api/cs/vds/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/homeRegion
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v1.17.6 — HomeRegion discovery endpoint, ported from evcc-io/evcc
  (vehicle/vw/api.go). Returns the per-VIN base URI for status/control
  calls. Used to route region-imported vehicles (US-spec VW EU, etc.)
  to the correct gateway instead of the default emea.bff.cariad.digital.

  Response shape (verified evcc-io/evcc source):
    {
      "homeRegion": {
        "baseUri": {
          "content": "https://emea.bff.cariad.digital"
        }
      }
    }

  For EU/standard vehicles the response baseUri.content equals our
  default _BASE. For region-routed vehicles it's a different gateway
  (e.g. mal-3a.prd.eu.dp.vwg-connect.com legacy MAL, or fal-... for
  Frankfurt). evcc rewrites mal-3a → fal- + /fs-car suffix in their
  HomeRegion() function, but we keep the returned URI verbatim.

  Implementation:
    custom_components/vag_connect/cariad/_home_region.py
    - resolve_home_region(client, vin, cache=...) -> str
    - HomeRegionCache: per-VIN result with 7d TTL
    - DEFAULT_BASE constant matches vw_eu._BASE

  Wire-up status: SCAFFOLDING ONLY in v1.17.6. Not yet integrated
  into vw_eu.py URL builders to avoid regressing the 99%-EU user
  base for an edge-case fix. Wire-in plan documented at top of
  _home_region.py.

  Privacy: VIN goes to the manufacturer's own discovery endpoint
  with the user's existing token. No third-party data leak.
}
